    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>In a national survey of 2,074 US parents conducted in March 2021, 35.9% reported their youngest child had been tested at least once for COVID-19. Parents\u2019 preferred testing venue choice was the pediatrician\u2019s office. Only half of parent surveyed (50.6%) reported that they would allow their child to be tested for COVID-19 at school/daycare if it was required.</jats:p>",
